@node description "Description"

 Nothing much to say about this  program  really.   It's a small command to
 display text in a standard  RECOVERY_ALERT.   The alert will appear yellow
 under WB2.0+ and red under previous kickstarts.
@endnode

**************************************************************************
@node usage "Usage"

 Syntax: Alert TEXTLINE/M

 All given parameters  will  be  centred  horizontally  and  its frame will
 automatically adjust to the number of lines.

 Typing just 'Alert' or 'Alert  ?'  will  display  the  copyright and the
 template.

 As an example, 'Alert  "Line  number  1"  Line_2  Line_3 "The last line!"'
 will  be displayed as:

 **************************************************************************
 *                              Line number 1                             *
 *                                  Line_2                                *
 *                                  Line_3                                *
 *                              The last line!                            *
 **************************************************************************
@endnode

